members.name: addressLine
members.doc: Main address line (usually street and number) as free text

members.name: city
members.doc: city name

members.name: country
members.doc: country code

members.name: postalCode
members.doc: zip/postal code

members.name: streetAddress
members.doc: a break down of the street to number and street name

members.name: subdivision
members.doc: subdivision (usually state or region) code according to ISO 3166-2

members.name: discounts
members.doc: discounts that apply to applicationFee

members.name: billingAddress
members.doc: Billing address associated with subscription to be used for payments.

members.name: collectionMethod
members.doc: Instructs how payments will be collected.

members.name: currency
members.doc: Currency of all subscription items prices. Three letter ISO currency code. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217

members.name: customBillingSchedule
members.doc: Billing Schedule to be defined in order to override default billing schedule

members.name: cycleAutoRenew
members.doc: If set to false, subscription will be canceled at the next billing cycle.

members.name: cycleDuration
members.doc: Duration of cycle. For example, 1 MONTH, 2 WEEKS, 7 DAY, 1 YEAR etc.

members.name: discounts
members.doc: General discount that applied to all items in the subscription

members.name: freeTrialDuration
members.doc: Definition of trial period

members.name: paymentMethod
members.doc: customer payment source to make recurring payments with

members.name: shippingFee
members.doc: Shipping costs collected each cycle

members.name: totalCycles
members.doc: Number of billing cycles. If not set subscription auto-renewed until cycle-auto-renew will be disabled.

members.name: currentCycle
members.doc: In which cycle subscription at the moment

members.name: freeTrialData
members.doc: Free trial data

members.name: latestPaymentData
members.doc: last payment details

members.name: nextBillingDate
members.doc: Date when charge will be for next billing cycle

members.name: previousBillingDate
members.doc: Previous Date charged for previous billing cycle

members.name: remainingCycles
members.doc: how many cycled are remaining, For auto-renew subscriptions is not set.

members.name: cancellationDate
members.doc: Subscription cancel date. Can contain a future or past date

members.name: initiator
members.doc: Initiator for cancellation

members.name: reason
members.doc: Reason for cancellation. Optional.

members.name: appId
members.doc: App id catalog belongs to. Optional. If not provided, assumed that belongs to subscription origin.app_id

members.name: catalogItemId
members.doc: External id of item in catalog.

members.name: cursor
members.doc: Cursor returned in last query response. Should not be provided on first page request

members.name: limit
members.doc:
The number of items to load.
Cursor token returned in the query response. To be used on the next query request, but not the first query request.

members.name: cyclesToPayOnCreation
members.doc:
Amount of cycles to be paid on Subscription creation, currently only cycles_to_pay_on_creation equals to 1 is supported
When used with Subscription.start_date, Subscription cycles will be paid on creation but Subscription will be activated in the future

members.name: cycleFrom
members.doc: The cycle from which the discount will apply

members.name: numberOfCycles
members.doc: Number of cycles to be applied on them discount. In order to apply a discount on all cycles until the end of the subscription, this field should be empty.

members.name: _id
members.doc: random GUID so clients can tell if event was already handled

members.name: entityFqdn
members.doc:
Assumes actions are also always typed to an entity_type
Example: wix.stores.catalog.product, wix.bookings.session, wix.payments.transaction

members.name: entityId
members.doc:
Assuming that all messages including Actions have id
Example: The id of the specific order, the id of a specific campaign

members.name: eventTime
members.doc: The time of the event. Useful if there was a delay in dipatching

members.name: originatedFrom
members.doc: If present, indicates the action that triggered the event.

members.name: slug
members.doc:
This is top level to ease client code dipatching of messages (switch on entity_fqdn+slug)
This is although the created/updated/deleted notion is duplication of the oneof types
Example: created/updated/deleted/started/completed/email_opened

members.name: triggeredByAnonymizeRequest
members.doc:
A field that should be set if this event was triggered by an anonymize request.
For example you must set it to true when sending an event as a result of a GDPR right to be forgotten request.
NOTE: This field is not relevant for `EntityCreatedEvent` but is located here for better ergonomics of consumers.

members.name: count
members.doc: Amount of units. For example,  1 MONTH, 1 YEAR, 2 WEEKS, etc. Optional. Default is 1.

members.name: unit
members.doc: Duration unit: DAY, WEEK, MONTH, YEAR

members.name: triggeredByUndelete
members.doc: Indicates the event was trigered on a previous deleted entity

members.name: currentEntityAsJson
members.doc:
Since platformized APIs only expose PATCH and not PUT we can't assume that the fields sent from the client are the actual diff.
This means that to generate a list of changed fields (as opposed to sent fields) one needs to traverse both objects.
We don't want to impose this on all developers and so we leave this traversal to the notification recipients which need it.

members.name: previousEntityAsJson
members.doc:
This field is currently part of the of the EntityUpdatedEvent msg, but scala/node libraries which implements the domain events standard
wont populate it / have any reference to it in the API.
The main reason for it is that fetching the old entity from the DB will have a performance hit on an update operation so unless truly needed,
the developer should send only the new (current) entity.
An additional reason is not wanting to send this additional entity over the wire (kafka) since in some cases it can be really big
Developers that must reflect the old entity will have to implement their own domain event sender mechanism which will follow the DomainEvent proto message.

members.name: itemPrice
members.doc:
Monetary amount. Decimal string with a period as a decimal separator (e.g., 3.99). Optionally, a single (-), to indicate that the amount is negative.
Price doesn't include tax, discounts & applicationFee

members.name: endDate
members.doc: Date when free trial ends

members.name: startDate
members.doc: Date when free trial starts

members.name: email
members.doc: Email associated with the address

members.name: _id
members.doc: Unique identifier of subscription item. Automatically generated and read-only.

members.name: applicationFee
members.doc: Application specific fee, positive value, optional (if application_fee == 0, don't include it to request). Only positive values.

members.name: catalogReference
members.doc: References to external product catalog data known to client.

members.name: category
members.doc: Category of item. Whether it is digital or physical one.

members.name: description
members.doc: Description of the item.

members.name: discounts
members.doc: Discounts applied on item price

members.name: metadata
members.doc:
Key / Value store to keep up to 10 additional values related to the subscription item.
Key max length = 50, Value max length = 200. Value can not be empty.
Should not include any sensitive or PII information.

members.name: name
members.doc: Name of the item. Typically product name.

members.name: pricingModel
members.doc: Pricing model of the item. Whether fixed price or dynamic price models.

members.name: quantity
members.doc: Amount of products

members.name: tax
members.doc: Tax, positive value, optional

members.name: limit
members.doc: Number of items to load.

members.name: offset
members.doc: Number of items to skip in the current sort order.

members.name: _id
members.doc: reference to payment source id stored in payments system

members.name: allowedProviderIds
members.doc: Allowed payment providers for Subscriptions, for example to limit subscriptions to be created only with "Wix Payments" provider.

members.name: cursorPaging
members.doc: Cursor token pointing to a page of results. Not used in the first request. Following requests use the cursor token and not `filter` or `sort`.

members.name: fields
members.doc: Array of projected fields. A list of specific field names to return. If `fieldsets` are also specified, the union of `fieldsets` and `fields` is returned.

members.name: fieldsets
members.doc: Array of named, predefined sets of projected fields. A array of predefined named sets of fields to be returned. Specifying multiple `fieldsets` will return the union of fields from all sets. If `fields` are also specified, the union of `fieldsets` and `fields` is returned.

members.name: filter
paging
members.doc: Paging options to limit and skip the number of items.

members.name: sort
members.doc:
Sort object in the following format:
`[{"fieldName":"sortField1","order":"ASC"},{"fieldName":"sortField2","order":"DESC"}]`

members.name: fieldName
members.doc: Name of the field to sort by.

members.name: order
members.doc: Sort order.

members.name: name
members.doc: street name

members.name: number
members.doc: street number

members.name: _createdDate
members.doc: Date when subscription was created

members.name: _id
members.doc: Subscription's unique id. Automatically generated and read-only.

members.name: _updatedDate
members.doc: Date when subscription was updated

members.name: billingSettings
members.doc: Billing details parameters including schedule, currency, etc.

members.name: billingStatus
members.doc: Includes many attributes about billing status of the subscription

members.name: cancellationInfo
members.doc: Information related to cancellation for already canceled subscription or scheduled for cancel

members.name: customer
members.doc: Customer information like id and identity type (member or contact)

members.name: description
members.doc: Subscription description. Optional.

members.name: endDate
members.doc:
Represents when the subscription will end, relevant for subscriptions with a termed period.
If not provided, will be calculated based on billing schedule. Should be empty for evergreen subscription.

members.name: items
members.doc: items, minSize is 1, maxSize is 100

members.name: metadata
members.doc:
Key / Value store to keep up to 10 additional values related to the subscription.
Key max length = 50, Value max length = 200. Value can not be empty.
Should not include any sensitive or PII information.

members.name: name
members.doc: Subscription name: minLength is 1, maxLength is 150

members.name: origin
members.doc: Business origin subscription is coming from. In site-level subscription it will be vertical app_id and entity_id

members.name: pauseInfo
members.doc: Information related to either paused subscription or scheduled for future pause

members.name: policies
members.doc: Restrictions on possible subscription actions. If not provided, default policies are all restrictions enabled.

members.name: revision
members.doc: Revision of subscription. Increments upon changes

members.name: shippingAddress
members.doc: Shipping address associated with subscription. At the moment used only for payments. Optional.

members.name: startDate
members.doc:
If start_date is set in the future: custom_billing_schedule.cycles_to_pay_on_creation should be set to 1
in order to pay on creation for first cycle, Subscription will be then activated in the future.
Future start_date is not supported for `SEND_INVOICE` CollectionMethod
If start_date is set in past, it means subscription was already started.

members.name: status
members.doc: Status of subscription

members.name: allowEndOfCycleCancellation
members.doc: Subscription can be canceled not only immediately, but also at end of billing cycle by turning off auto-renew

members.name: businessCanExtend
members.doc: Subscription end date can be updated by business

members.name: customerCanCancel
members.doc: Subscription can be canceled by the customer who bought it

members.name: amount
members.doc: Tax amount to charge for this item

members.name: percentage
members.doc: Tax percentage to charge for item price and application fee, can't be use together with global discount amount

members.name: applicationFee
members.doc: Total application fee

members.name: discount
members.doc: Total discount

members.name: shippingFee
members.doc: Total shipping fee

members.name: subtotal
members.doc: Subtotal of all line items: (itemPrice X quantity)

members.name: tax
members.doc: Total tax

members.name: totalPrice
members.doc: Total price = (itemPrice X quantity) + totalTax + shipping - totalDiscount + totalApplicationFee
